# TMLSN Project Context

Reference: `tmlsn_all_documentation (1).md` — the canonical spec for features and requirements.

## One-Line Definition

TMLSN starts as useful tools (nutrition, workout tracking, prompt vault), then becomes an integrated operating system—where an AI version of us coaches the user using their real data, constraints, and prompt-backed action plans, while also notifying them when new newsletter and YouTube content drops.

## Product Thesis

Apps are becoming "hosts": one place that bundles tools + content + coaching. TMLSN direction: start with tools, evolve into an integrated system. **MVP focus:** ship useful tools fast that connect to content strategy and provide a clear upgrade path.

## MVP Scope (V1.0)

### Layer A: Tools (MVP)
- **Calorie/Nutrition Tracker:** Calories, P/C/F, electrolytes (Mg, Ca, Na, K), meal structure (B/L/D/Snacks), water intake, metric/US units, food database integration.
- **Workout Tracker:** Exercise name, sets, reps, weight; rest timer (toggle, countdown, push on complete); pre-loaded TMLSN Split; free-form logging; progressive overload history.
- **Prompt Vault:** Text storage, copy-to-clipboard, source link attribution, weekly content cadence, user usage history.

### Layer B: Prompts (MVP)
- Actionable advice must be backed by a usable prompt. App = execution engine: post explains, app provides prompt, user saves/runs/reuses.

### Layer C: Notifications (MVP)
- **Distribution only:** Newsletter and YouTube drop alerts. No behavioral/coaching triggers in MVP.

### Layer D: Content (MVP)
- Mastering Aesthetics course in-app or deep-linked with session context.

### Layer E: Coaching
- Future scope. AI coach, constraint-aware, data-integrated.

